   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 📚 Build Mamba SSM from Scratch - Part 2: The Parallel Scan Algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Colab Ready**: This notebook runs on Google Colab with GPU support!\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objectives**:\n",
    "1. Understand why sequential SSM computation is slow\n",
    "2. Learn the associative scan algorithm\n",
    "3. Implement parallel scan for SSM\n",
    "4. Compare sequential vs parallel performance\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. The Problem: Sequential Computation is Slow\n",
    "\n",
    "In the previous notebook, we implemented the SSM as a **sequential recurrence**:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "for t in range(seq_len):\n",
    "    h = A_bar * h + B_bar * x_t\n",
    "    y = C * h\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This is **O(seq_len)** sequentially, but:\n",
    "- ❌ Cannot parallelize across time steps\n",
    "- ❌ GPU utilization is poor (one token at a time)\n",
    "- ❌ Slow on long sequences\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Insight**: If we can reformulate the recurrence as an **associative scan**, we can compute the entire sequence in **O(log n)** parallel steps!\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Mathematical Reformulation\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.1 The SSM as an Associative Scan\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's rewrite the SSM recurrence to expose its associative structure.\n",
    "\n",
    "The SSM step is:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "h_k = \\bar{A} h_{k-1} + \\bar{B} x_k\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's unroll this for a few steps:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{aligned}\n",
    "h_1 &= \\bar{A} h_0 + \\bar{B} x_1 \\\\\n",
    "h_2 &= \\bar{A} h_1 + \\bar{B} x_2 \\\\\n",
    "     &= \\bar{A}(\\bar{A} h_0 + \\bar{B} x_1) + \\bar{B} x_2 \\\\\n",
    "     &= \\bar{A}^2 h_0 + \\bar{A}\\bar{B} x_1 + \\bar{B} x_2 \\\\\n",
    "h_3 &= \\bar{A} h_2 + \\bar{B} x_3 \\\\\n",
    "     &= \\bar{A}^3 h_0 + \\bar{A}^2\\bar{B} x_1 + \\bar{A}\\bar{B} x_2 + \\bar{B} x_3\n",
    "\\end{aligned}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "We can see a pattern! Each $h_k$ is a **linear combination** of all previous inputs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2 The Scan Pair\n",
    "\n",
    "Define a **scan pair** $(a_k, b_k)$:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "a_k = \\bar{A}^k, \\quad b_k = \\sum_{i=0}^{k-1} \\bar{A}^i \\bar{B} x_{k-i}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Now, the recurrence can be written as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "(a_k, b_k) = (a_{k-1}, b_{k-1}) \\oplus (\\bar{A}, \\bar{B} x_k)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where the **binary operator** $\\oplus$ is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "(a_{k-1}, b_{k-1}) \\oplus (a_k, b_k) = (a_{k-1} \\cdot a_k, a_{k-1} \\cdot b_k + b_{k-1})\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**This is associative!** $(a \\oplus b) \\oplus c = a \\oplus (b \\oplus c)$\n",
    "\n",
    "So we can use a **parallel scan** to compute all states in O(log n) time!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.3 Why Associativity Matters\n",
    "\n",
    "The associative property allows us to **parallelize**:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Sequential (O(n)):\n",
    "h0 → h1 → h2 → h3 → h4 → h5 → h6 → h7\n",
    "\n",
    "Parallel Scan (O(log n)):\n",
    "    h0 ──┬── h1   h2 ──┬── h3   h4 ──┬── h5   h6 ──┬── h7\n",
    "        │      │       │      │       │      │       │\n",
    "        ▼      ▼       ▼      ▼       ▼      ▼       ▼\n",
    "    combine  combine  combine  combine\n",
    "        │              │              │              │\n",
    "        ▼              ▼              ▼              ▼\n",
    "    h0-1          h2-3          h4-5          h6-7\n",
    "        │              │              │              │\n",
    "        ▼              ▼              ▼              ▼\n",
    "    combine          combine          combine\n",
    "        │                              │\n",
    "        ▼                              ▼\n",
    "    h0-3                              h4-7\n",
    "        │                              │\n",
    "        ▼                              ▼\n",
    "    combine (final result in O(log n) steps!)\n",
    "        │\n",
    "        ▼\n",
    "    h0-7\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
